cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a deep network that combines contextual features and spatial information, which involves machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The proposed network uses attention mechanisms, which are a popular topic in deep learning research, and can be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on two datasets, which involves performance metrics and benchmarking, and can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
